<sec>
<st>
 Biography </st>
<p>

Vance was born in <village wordnetid="108672738" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../687/8687.xml">
Detroit</link></village>
, <country wordnetid="108544813" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../859/18859.xml">
Michigan</link></country>
. He attended <school wordnetid="108276720" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../572/1020572.xml">
Detroit Country Day School</link></school>
, a fee-paying <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../970/299970.xml">
university-preparatory school</link>, and later graduated from <university wordnetid="108286163" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../501/18426501.xml">
Harvard University</link></university>
 with a bachelor of arts <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../241/167241.xml">
degree</link>. While attending Harvard, Vance was already working as an actor at the <link>
Boston Shakespeare Company</link>. He earned a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../486/894486.xml">
Master of Fine Arts</link> degree later at <school wordnetid="108276720" confidence="0.8">
<educational_institution wordnetid="108276342" confidence="0.8">
<institution wordnetid="108053576" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../450/695450.xml">
Yale School of Drama</link></institution>
</educational_institution>
</school>
.</p>
<p>

He is on the Board of Directors for <school wordnetid="108276720" confidence="0.8">
<educational_institution wordnetid="108276342" confidence="0.8">
<institution wordnetid="108053576" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../611/8218611.xml">
